miscConds.notes:
Defendant shall pay supervisory fees to the Department of Corrections;
Defendant shall complete any/all counseling, evaluations, assessments, and follow-up as deemed appropriate;
Defendant shall not possess/consume any alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Submit DNA sample.
Defendant shall Submit to Observed Random Urinalysis at least twice a month.
No contact with victim or victim's family.
Defendant shall maintain full time employment.  Should defendant become unemployed he shall apply at 20 businesses/month that are hiring and file work search affidavits.
If defendant revoked, court shall impose a fine for $1000.00 plus court costs.
Probation sentence is consecutive to Count 1 and shall begin after completion of jail sentence.
